# Common Oracle Performance Dashboards
##### Using Oracle AWR views and cx_Oracle library for read data from database

%pyspark
v_user=z.input("User name", "User_name")
v_pwd=z.input("User pwd", "Pwd")
v_conn=z.input("Connection", "host:port/sid")
import cx_Oracle

# Init connection OracleDBconnection 
def init_db(usr,pwd,conn):
    db = cx_Oracle.connect(usr,pwd,conn)
    return db

# Execute Oracle SQl with param and create SparkTable
def exec_Oracle_SQL(conn, sql, params, spark_table_name):
    cur=conn.cursor()
    if params == None:
        res=cur.execute(sql)
    else:
        res=cur.execute(sql, params)
    res_list = res.fetchall()
    if len(res_list) == 0:
        return spark_table_name+". Empty dataset. SparkTable coudn't be created"
    sqlContext.registerDataFrameAsTable(sqlContext.createDataFrame(res_list, [x[0] for x in res.description] ),spark_table_name)
    return spark_table_name+'. Register spark table succsessful'

db_con = init_db(v_user, v_pwd, v_conn)
res=exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, "select * from dual", None, "dual")
if res == 1:
    print("Connection established")
cur = db_con.cursor()
cur.execute("select distinct dbid, dbid||' v.'||VERSION||' dbname='||DB_NAME||', host_name='||HOST_NAME||', platform='||PLATFORM_NAME||', start_time='||to_char(STARTUP_TIME, 'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi') description,STARTUP_TIME from dba_hist_database_instance order by 3 desc")
dbid_list = cur.fetchall()

%pyspark
v_dbid= z.select ("DB for analytics in AWR repository:", [(x[0],x[1]) for x in dbid_list])
named_params ={'dbid':v_dbid}
cur.execute("select snap_id snap_id, to_char(end_interval_time, 'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi') as end_interval_time from dba_hist_snapshot where dbid=:dbid order by 1",named_params)
a=cur.fetchall()

%pyspark
snap_beg= z.select ("Time begin(snap_beg):", a)
snap_end= z.select ("Time end(snap_end):", a)
inst = z.input("Instance number(inst) (* for all)","*")

%pyspark
DB_TIME_sql = "\
with \
    snap_time as (select to_char(max(end_interval_time),'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi:ss') t, snap_id \
                    from DBA_HIST_snapshot \
                    where dbid=:dbid and decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) = instance_number and \
                            snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end \
                    group by snap_id), \
    wait_time as    (select snap_id,  \
                        'Wait' as time_class ,  \
                        sum(time_waited_delta)/1000000 as value  \
                        from (select time_waited_micro - first_value(time_waited_micro) over (partition by dbid, instance_number, event_id order by snap_id ROWS 1 PRECEDING)  as time_waited_delta, \
                                        DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT.* \
                                    from DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT  \
                                    where   dbid=:dbid and  \
                                            decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number  and \
	                                        snap_id in (select snap_id from  snap_time)  \
                                            and  wait_class <>'Idle')  \
                        group by snap_id \
                    ), \
    db_time as      (select snap_id, 'DBTime' as time_class, sum(value)/1000000 as value from \
                        (select snap_id,value - first_value(value) over(partition by dbid, instance_number, stat_id order by snap_id ROWS 1 PRECEDING) as value from dba_hist_sys_time_model \
                            where   dbid=:dbid and  \
                                    decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number  and \
	                                snap_id in (select snap_id from  snap_time) \
                                    and stat_name ='DB time')  \
                        group by snap_id  \
                    ),  \
    cpu_time as     (select snap_id, 'CPU' as time_class, sum(value)/1000000 as value from   \
                        (select snap_id, value - first_value(value) over(partition by dbid, instance_number, stat_id order by snap_id ROWS 1 PRECEDING) as value from dba_hist_sys_time_model \
                            where   dbid=:dbid and  \
                                    decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number  and \
	                                snap_id in (select snap_id from  snap_time) \
                                    and stat_name ='DB CPU') \
                        group by snap_id \
                    )   \
select * from ( select snap_time.t, wait_time.snap_id,wait_time.time_class, wait_time.value  from snap_time, wait_time where snap_time.snap_id = wait_time.snap_id \
union all \
select snap_time.t, db_time.snap_id,db_time.time_class, db_time.value  from snap_time, db_time where snap_time.snap_id = db_time.snap_id  \
union all  \
select snap_time.t, cpu_time.snap_id,cpu_time.time_class, cpu_time.value  from snap_time, cpu_time where snap_time.snap_id = cpu_time.snap_id  \
        )  \
order by snap_id  "

named_params ={'dbid':v_dbid, 'inst':inst, 'snap_beg':snap_beg, 'snap_end':snap_end}
exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, DB_TIME_sql, named_params, "db_time_analytics")

WAIT_TIME_sql = "\
select stat.wait_class, stat.value,  snap_time.t, stat.snap_id \
 from (select to_char(max(end_interval_time),'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi:ss') t, snap_id \
from DBA_HIST_snapshot where dbid=:dbid and decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number and snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end  \
group by snap_id) snap_time, \
(select snap_id,  \
       wait_class, round(sum(time_waited_delta)/1000000) as value  \
       from ( \
select time_waited_micro - first_value(time_waited_micro) over (partition by dbid, instance_number, event_id order by snap_id ROWS 1 PRECEDING)  as time_waited_delta, \
 DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT.* \
  from DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT  \
     where dbid=:dbid and  decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number and \
     snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end and  wait_class <>'Idle' \
          ) \
   group by snap_id, wait_class   \
    order by snap_id, wait_class) stat \
     where stat.snap_id = snap_time.snap_id order by snap_time.t \
"

exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, WAIT_TIME_sql, named_params, "wait_time_analytics")

#List of wait class for choose detail wait analytics
WAIT_LIST_CLASS_SQL="select distinct wait_class from DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT where dbid=:dbid and  decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number and snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end order by 1"
cur = db_con.cursor()
cur.execute(WAIT_LIST_CLASS_SQL,named_params)
wait_class_list = cur.fetchall()

from DBA_HIST_SYSMETRIC_SUMMARY where  dbid=:dbid and metric_id =:metric_id  and snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end and instance_number = decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) order by 2"
METRIC_HISTORY_SQL = "\

                  (VALUE - first_value(VALUE) over (partition by s.dbid, s.instance_number, s.STAT_ID order by s.snap_id ROWS 1 PRECEDING)) as value, stat_name \

%md
# SQL Analytics
Dashboards for analyzing sql performance

%pyspark
SQL_rank_type = z.select("Choose TOP SQL Category", [("rank_time","Elapsed"),("rank_cpu","CPU"),("rank_io","User I/O"),("rank_cc","Concurrency"),("rank_cl","Cluster"),("rank_ap","Application"),("rank_java","Java"),("rank_pl","PLSQL")])
SQL_rank = z.input("Input tops threshold for choosen category","50")
sql_top_params = named_params.copy()
sql_top_params.update({"rank_type":SQL_rank_type, "rank":SQL_rank}) 
TOPSQL_SQL = "\
select * from \
(select * from  \
(select sql_id, dbid,  \
       executions, \
       elapsed_time, \
       CPU_TIME, \
       IOWAIT, \
       APWAIT, \
       CCWAIT, \
       PLSEXEC, \
       JAVEXEC, \
       CLWAIT,  \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by elapsed_time DESC) rank_time, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by CPU_TIME DESC) rank_cpu, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by IOWAIT DESC) rank_io, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by CCWAIT DESC) rank_cc, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by APWAIT DESC) rank_ap, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by PLSEXEC DESC) rank_pl, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by CLWAIT DESC) rank_cl, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by JAVEXEC DESC) rank_java \
    from  \
(select sql_id, max(dbid) dbid, sum(executions_delta) executions, \
       round(sum(elapsed_time_delta)/1000000) elapsed_time, \
       round(sum(CPU_TIME_DELTA)/1000000) CPU_TIME, \
       round(sum(IOWAIT_DELTA)/1000000) IOWAIT, \
       round(sum(APWAIT_DELTA)/1000000) APWAIT, \
       round(sum(CCWAIT_DELTA)/1000000) CCWAIT, \
       round(sum(PLSEXEC_TIME_DELTA)/1000000) PLSEXEC, \
       round(sum(JAVEXEC_TIME_DELTA)/1000000) JAVEXEC, \
       round(sum(CLWAIT_DELTA)/1000000) CLWAIT \
       from dba_hist_sqlstat  where dbid=:dbid \
            and snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end \
            and instance_number = decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst)  \
       group by sql_id) \
       ) \
        where  \
           decode(:rank_type,'rank_cpu',rank_cpu,'rank_io',rank_io,'rank_cc',rank_cc,'rank_cl',rank_cl, \
                        'rank_ap',rank_ap,'rank_java',rank_java,'rank_pl',rank_pl,'rank_time', rank_time ) < :rank    \
        ) \
 UNPIVOT ( v_time FOR wait_class IN (ELAPSED_TIME, \
       CPU_TIME, \
       IOWAIT, \
       APWAIT, \
       CCWAIT, \
       PLSEXEC, \
       JAVEXEC, \
       CLWAIT))    "
                        
print(exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, TOPSQL_SQL, sql_top_params, "sqltop_analytics"))
